column4: Nvidia shares set record as Volta chips ensure future growth
column5: Shares of Nvidia Corp  hit a record on Friday  after it posted stellar quarterly results powered by higher demand for graphics chips used in gaming and data centers  and the rapid adoption of its new Volta chips for AI and driverless cars.

column4: US STOCKS SNAPSHOT-Wall St ends little changed; Apple  Intel drag
column5: NEW YORK  Nov 10 Wall Street ended nearly unchanged on Friday  with losses in Intel and Apple as investors worried about the future of promised corporate tax cuts following dueling plans unveiled by Republican U.S. lawmakers.

column4: HK's Razer IPO raises $528 mln amid heavy retail demand
column5: HONG KONG  Nov 10 Razer Inc  backed by Intel Corp and Hong Kong billionaire Li Ka-shing  on Friday set its initial public offering price at HK$3.88 per share  confirming a report by a Reuters's publication that the gaming hardware maker had priced its shares near the top of a range.

column4: Breakingviews - Viewsroom: Broadcom $130 bln bid signals market top
column5: NEW YORK (Reuters Breakingviews) - The chipmaker’s hostile tilt at Qualcomm is a rare aggressive move in the sector. Qualcomm has its own issues  awaiting approval for its NXP deal and fighting Apple in court. It all suggests the tech sector is too frothy. Plus: Is Hong Kong losing its moxie as a financial center?

column4: LPC: Lenders to embrace a record Broadcom bridge loan
column5: NEW YORK  Nov 10 Banks are eager to open their wallets for what could be the biggest syndicated loan financing ever for an investment-grade acquisition  if chipmaker Broadcom’s unsolicited US$103bn bid to buy Qualcomm is accepted.
